The three stages of the core RAG pipeline are: 
(1) Indexing, where documents are split into chunks and converted to vector embeddings; 
(2) Retrieval, where user queries are embedded and compared against the document embeddings using similarity search; 
(3) Generation, where the retrieved context is concatenated with the user query and passed to a language model for answer synthesis. [Fundamentals_of_RAG.pdf, page 2]
